1
00:01:07,819 --> 00:01:12,039
(Doom at Your Service)

2
00:01:12,306 --> 00:01:15,274
(All characters, locations, organizations, religions, )

3
00:01:15,275 --> 00:01:17,946
(and incidents in this drama are fictional.)

4
00:01:43,505 --> 00:01:44,606
Tak Dong Kyung.

5
00:01:46,375 --> 00:01:47,975
How do you know my name?

6
00:01:48,276 --> 00:01:49,375
Who are you?

7
00:01:50,246 --> 00:01:51,485
Then, who are you?

8
00:01:58,485 --> 00:01:59,794
It's cold tonight.

9
00:01:59,795 --> 00:02:02,595
Why did she leave? She could catch a cold. Goodness.

10
00:02:02,596 --> 00:02:03,726
Tak Dong Kyung.

11
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:07,294
First floor. The doors are closing.

12
00:02:07,295 --> 00:02:08,565
Going down.

13
00:02:12,205 --> 00:02:14,475
- What was that about? - My aunt.

14
00:02:14,476 --> 00:02:16,144
If she sees us, things will get complicated.

15
00:02:16,145 --> 00:02:17,975
If we want to talk, I can't let her catch us.

16
00:02:17,976 --> 00:02:19,106
Talk about what?

17
00:02:20,576 --> 00:02:22,545
Aren't you here because you needed to talk to me?

18
00:02:23,015 --> 00:02:24,314
I doubt that you came back because you missed me...

19
00:02:24,315 --> 00:02:25,616
since we just saw each other.

20
00:02:28,616 --> 00:02:30,485
Why did you ask me who I was?

21
00:02:30,856 --> 00:02:32,385
You even know my name.

22
00:02:32,386 --> 00:02:33,595
Then, what about your question?

23
00:02:34,095 --> 00:02:37,295
I explained to you who I am and what I do.

24
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:41,166
I don't know.

25
00:02:41,996 --> 00:02:43,966
Something feels weird.

26
00:02:46,935 --> 00:02:48,205
Second basement floor.

27
00:02:50,606 --> 00:02:52,705
- Where are we going? - To the parking lot.

28
00:02:53,015 --> 00:02:54,446
This will be a long conversation.

29
00:03:00,616 --> 00:03:03,655
(Episode 13)

30
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:14,936
I need to ask you something.

31
00:03:17,166 --> 00:03:18,906
It's cold out here. Let's talk inside.

32
00:03:19,906 --> 00:03:21,076
I can't do that inside.

33
00:03:24,006 --> 00:03:25,205
I'll lose there...

34
00:03:26,376 --> 00:03:27,675
because it's your turf.

35
00:03:28,476 --> 00:03:30,446
- Then, this place works for you? - No.

36
00:03:32,015 --> 00:03:33,555
There isn't such a place.

37
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:36,786
I picked this place...

38
00:03:38,055 --> 00:03:39,925
because it'd be easier to run away if I wanted.

39
00:03:45,066 --> 00:03:46,566
Let's stop skirting around it now.

40
00:03:56,036 --> 00:03:57,946
- Joo Ik. - Yes.

41
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,615
Did you kiss her?

42
00:04:02,545 --> 00:04:03,715
Did you...

43
00:04:06,656 --> 00:04:07,916
kiss her 10 years ago?

44
00:04:09,686 --> 00:04:11,286
- Yes. - Why?

45
00:04:11,525 --> 00:04:12,786
To get her out of there.

46
00:04:13,856 --> 00:04:15,395
So you two wouldn't get back together.

47
00:04:18,196 --> 00:04:19,265
Why?

48
00:04:22,436 --> 00:04:24,265
She cried there every single day.

49
00:04:25,465 --> 00:04:27,305
If I didn't make her leave that day,

50
00:04:27,606 --> 00:04:31,106
she would have cried, sitting on that step for days and months.

51
00:04:32,705 --> 00:04:33,916
I didn't want her...

52
00:04:34,576 --> 00:04:36,715
to come back again, sit there, and cry.

53
00:04:39,515 --> 00:04:41,786
- That's why I did it. - Did you think about me?

54
00:04:44,055 --> 00:04:45,485
- Did you? - I did.

55
00:04:46,395 --> 00:04:47,656
All the more reason why I did it.

56
00:04:48,995 --> 00:04:51,525
You knew that she was waiting for you.

57
00:04:52,295 --> 00:04:54,165
You knew, but you never went out to see her...

58
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:55,365
because you were embarrassed.

59
00:04:56,636 --> 00:04:58,234
You left Korea as if you were never going to come back,

60
00:04:58,235 --> 00:05:00,305
but you came back only after a few months because it was tough.

61
00:05:01,036 --> 00:05:02,305
You didn't want her to find out.

62
00:05:07,175 --> 00:05:08,446
Say something.

63
00:05:09,175 --> 00:05:11,085
Curse me out if you want. I'll handle it.

64
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:12,816
I won't run away.

65
00:05:13,555 --> 00:05:15,156
Why are you brutally honest?

66
00:05:15,886 --> 00:05:17,256
You could have avoided answering it,

67
00:05:18,155 --> 00:05:19,855
apologized, and moved on.

68
00:05:21,996 --> 00:05:23,296
You have a way with words too.

69
00:05:24,696 --> 00:05:26,436
Why are you brutally honest with me?

70
00:05:27,436 --> 00:05:28,636
Because I like you.

71
00:05:33,835 --> 00:05:34,876
You are...

72
00:05:35,605 --> 00:05:37,446
one of a few people I actually like.

73
00:05:38,405 --> 00:05:40,546
I don't want to be a coward in front of you.

74
00:05:43,215 --> 00:05:44,715
I've hidden it for too long.

75
00:05:45,915 --> 00:05:47,056
And all these years,

76
00:05:50,285 --> 00:05:52,025
it had been bothering me too.

77
00:05:58,826 --> 00:06:00,066
This is so annoying.

78
00:06:05,806 --> 00:06:08,636
You still make me feel worthless even in this moment.

79
00:06:09,975 --> 00:06:11,546
You're so annoying.

80
00:06:14,275 --> 00:06:15,446
Where are you going?

81
00:06:16,446 --> 00:06:18,285
- To the cafe. - Why?

82
00:06:19,046 --> 00:06:21,285
I don't think I can sleep in the same house with you tonight.

83
00:06:28,626 --> 00:06:30,296
I regret every moment of it.

84
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:34,996
Running away, taking too long,

85
00:06:36,535 --> 00:06:37,705
and asking you.

86
00:06:39,975 --> 00:06:41,006
Everything.

87
00:06:58,725 --> 00:07:00,155
I was crying.

88
00:07:02,395 --> 00:07:04,394
I looked in the mirror after I came back.

89
00:07:04,395 --> 00:07:05,725
And I was crying.

90
00:07:06,835 --> 00:07:08,595
But I didn't even know I was crying.

91
00:07:08,936 --> 00:07:12,636
When I looked in the mirror, I was crying.

92
00:07:16,746 --> 00:07:18,446
Why was I crying?

93
00:07:27,616 --> 00:07:28,715
Get in.

94
00:07:30,826 --> 00:07:31,925
Where are we going?

95
00:07:31,926 --> 00:07:33,525
You'll be safe. Get in.

96
00:07:40,436 --> 00:07:41,436
Have you seen...

97
00:07:42,835 --> 00:07:45,464
a girl who's about this tall and has hair coming up to here?

98
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,806
Have you?

99
00:07:48,905 --> 00:07:51,245
A girl who's about this tall and has hair coming up to here?

100
00:07:51,246 --> 00:07:52,305
That description fits so many girls.

101
00:07:52,306 --> 00:07:54,446
Have you met someone like her at the hospital?

102
00:07:55,845 --> 00:07:58,415
- Are you talking about her? - Have you met her?

103
00:07:59,116 --> 00:08:00,455
What did she do to you?

104
00:08:00,756 --> 00:08:02,415
She didn't do anything. I did something for her.

105
00:08:02,715 --> 00:08:04,585
I opened a bottle for her.

106
00:08:05,426 --> 00:08:06,455
What else?

107
00:08:07,225 --> 00:08:08,225
What else?

108
00:08:10,996 --> 00:08:13,594
After that, she thanked me and told me to go to the rooftop.

109
00:08:13,595 --> 00:08:14,835
She said the view there was nice.

110
00:08:16,066 --> 00:08:18,035
- Anything else other than that? - No.

111
00:08:19,705 --> 00:08:22,306
Think again. I'm sure she did something to you.

112
00:08:23,376 --> 00:08:24,445
What did she do?

113
00:08:24,446 --> 00:08:26,446
That's what I don't know. So think again.

114
00:08:34,715 --> 00:08:35,785
I don't know.

115
00:08:37,756 --> 00:08:39,055
What do you know then?

116
00:08:39,056 --> 00:08:41,426
What does she have to do with us?

117
00:08:41,556 --> 00:08:42,796
Does she know me?

118
00:08:43,296 --> 00:08:45,224
I can't remember her either?

119
00:08:45,225 --> 00:08:47,065
Perhaps, your brain has just gone bad, not sick.

120
00:08:47,066 --> 00:08:48,496
No need to talk about yourself now.

121
00:08:49,796 --> 00:08:52,465
Right. I'm not exactly kind.

122
00:08:55,236 --> 00:08:57,145
All good, right? It's my turn now.

123
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:00,915
You weren't crying?

124
00:09:04,585 --> 00:09:05,845
Why won't you answer my question?

125
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:08,655
I asked if you weren't crying. Was I the only one who cried?

126
00:09:12,455 --> 00:09:13,955
I'm not done with my questions yet.

127
00:09:15,556 --> 00:09:17,296
Who were you calling earlier?

128
00:09:17,696 --> 00:09:20,196
Exactly. That's really weird.

129
00:09:20,636 --> 00:09:21,936
I was crying.

130
00:09:22,196 --> 00:09:24,136
But I couldn't get that thought out of my head.

131
00:09:24,736 --> 00:09:27,736
"I must call you."

132
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,741
- "You"? - But...

133
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:34,511
I don't know who that person is.

134
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:37,250
That person's number is saved on my cell phone.

135
00:09:37,251 --> 00:09:38,820
But I have no idea who it is.

136
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:43,290
Call that number again.

137
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:51,929
(Call log)

138
00:09:51,930 --> 00:09:53,430
(Human)

139
00:10:01,011 --> 00:10:04,081
Whoever it is isn't picking up. Whose number is this?

140
00:10:06,711 --> 00:10:09,680
"Human". Who's "Human"?

141
00:10:10,751 --> 00:10:13,550
Who knows? At least I know it's not me.

142
00:10:13,991 --> 00:10:15,091
I should go now.

143
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:16,790
What about me?

144
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:18,560
What?

145
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:20,230
Aren't you going to drive me back?

146
00:10:20,231 --> 00:10:21,330
It's nearby.

147
00:10:21,331 --> 00:10:22,831
Walk back. It's only five minutes by foot.

148
00:10:25,861 --> 00:10:28,930
Gosh, if he were human I would've taught him a lesson.

149
00:10:34,341 --> 00:10:35,940
Who could it be?

150
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:37,910
"Human".

151
00:10:44,881 --> 00:10:46,280
Why do you fall so easily?

152
00:10:46,550 --> 00:10:48,390
Watch where you're going.

153
00:10:48,721 --> 00:10:49,750
I thought you were leaving.

154
00:10:49,751 --> 00:10:51,020
Yes, I was on my way.

155
00:10:53,890 --> 00:10:56,800
My gosh. Seriously.

156
00:10:57,461 --> 00:10:59,160
He must be mad in the head.

157
00:11:23,890 --> 00:11:25,591
(Missed call: Dong Kyung)

158
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:26,279
(Business proposal)

159
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:29,091
(Sales and Marketing Plan)

160
00:12:30,991 --> 00:12:33,491
(The Story of Genius Minds, Welcome to Genius)

161
00:12:35,261 --> 00:12:38,960
(Friday, Saturday, Sunday)

162
00:12:38,961 --> 00:12:41,630
(My love confession is either always too early or too late.)

163
00:12:41,631 --> 00:12:43,600
(My love confession...)

164
00:12:43,601 --> 00:12:47,510
(is either always too early or too late.)

165
00:12:47,511 --> 00:12:49,341
(From "The Romantic Egoists")

166
00:12:56,874 --> 00:12:58,114
My gosh, he startled me.

167
00:13:01,451 --> 00:13:03,991
Mr. Lee. Mr. Lee!

168
00:13:06,991 --> 00:13:09,131
Oh, hey. Gosh.

169
00:13:09,761 --> 00:13:10,800
You're here.

170
00:13:10,961 --> 00:13:12,299
Did you sleep here?

171
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,201
- Yes. - Why?

172
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:16,530
Did you fight with your friend?

173
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,640
No.

174
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:21,711
Then what?

175
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:23,640
We're still fighting.

176
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,981
They're always fighting. It's like they're a married couple.

177
00:13:32,650 --> 00:13:34,991
Here's the business proposal you asked for. Take a look.

178
00:13:41,890 --> 00:13:43,899
Did you fight with Hyun Kyu?

179
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:46,871
What are you talking about? Does it look like I fought with him?

180
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:49,371
I guess you guys didn't have a fistfight yet.

181
00:13:49,770 --> 00:13:52,139
I'm not going to fight him. Plus, I'd win anyway.

182
00:13:52,140 --> 00:13:55,170
Is that so? You think you'll win? Are you sure about that?

183
00:13:56,410 --> 00:13:57,481
So you lost.

184
00:13:57,910 --> 00:14:00,650
- We haven't fought yet. - Then go ahead and fight.

185
00:14:00,981 --> 00:14:03,451
You won't know who will win until you actually fight him.

186
00:14:03,481 --> 00:14:06,081
Do you want me to go around fighting people?

187
00:14:06,581 --> 00:14:09,150
Do you know why I adore Hyun Kyu so much?

188
00:14:09,621 --> 00:14:12,190
Maybe it's because he grew up as an athlete,

189
00:14:12,261 --> 00:14:16,060
but behind that smile of his, I can tell he's very competitive.

190
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:18,201
I really like that about him.

191
00:14:19,701 --> 00:14:21,100
Whatever.

192
00:14:21,101 --> 00:14:22,601
You're nothing like him.

193
00:14:23,101 --> 00:14:24,500
When he's in for a competition,

194
00:14:24,501 --> 00:14:27,140
he does everything he can to win, but look at you.

195
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:29,471
You always just yield as if it doesn't even matter.

196
00:14:30,581 --> 00:14:32,240
I bet he's pretty irritated though.

197
00:14:32,241 --> 00:14:34,650
You always let him win without even putting up a fight.

198
00:14:38,951 --> 00:14:40,420
Things are a bit different this time.

199
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:42,451
How so?

200
00:14:43,121 --> 00:14:44,621
We're not fighting.

201
00:14:45,261 --> 00:14:46,721
But I need to take something from him.

202
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:48,761
Really?

203
00:14:50,961 --> 00:14:52,731
Then I guess you'll win this time.

204
00:14:54,831 --> 00:14:59,269
I've never seen you fail to get what you want.

205
00:14:59,270 --> 00:15:00,471
And the same goes with this.

206
00:15:01,211 --> 00:15:02,371
I'm looking forward to it.

207
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:05,710
If you lose but refuse to admit to it,

208
00:15:05,711 --> 00:15:07,210
that would make you a bad mentor.

209
00:15:07,211 --> 00:15:09,350
But if he loses and doesn't back off,

210
00:15:09,351 --> 00:15:10,721
that would mean you didn't teach him well.

211
00:15:14,451 --> 00:15:16,621
So whatever happens, it's all on me.

212
00:15:16,861 --> 00:15:19,120
If you're going to be the bad guy no matter the result,

213
00:15:19,121 --> 00:15:20,631
you should at least win.

214
00:15:35,410 --> 00:15:36,511
You did this, didn't you?

215
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:43,081
What exactly is my relationship with her?

216
00:15:48,491 --> 00:15:49,920
You're not going to tell me?

217
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:54,760
If you don't want to tell me, then don't.

218
00:15:54,761 --> 00:15:56,591
I'll figure it out myself.

219
00:15:57,861 --> 00:16:00,001
I didn't think you'd tell me anyway.

220
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:04,971
Instead, don't resent me even if something happens.

221
00:16:31,631 --> 00:16:33,900
You kept going on about ghosts,

222
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:36,670
and now you're even watching ghost dramas?

223
00:16:38,601 --> 00:16:39,799
What? What did you say?

224
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:42,169
You're awfully energetic for someone who's fasting.

225
00:16:42,170 --> 00:16:45,110
Why are you starting the day watching such a scary drama?

226
00:16:45,111 --> 00:16:47,680
Aunt, I'm not watching this for fun.

227
00:16:47,810 --> 00:16:49,351
I'm studying right now.

228
00:16:50,420 --> 00:16:54,091
I need to study ghosts in order to... Wait a minute.

229
00:16:54,451 --> 00:16:56,920
What? Why does this situation feel so familiar?

230
00:16:57,690 --> 00:17:00,221
- My goodness. - Is it a deja vu?

231
00:17:07,231 --> 00:17:09,170
What? What are you doing here?

232
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:11,769
Hey, watch it. Why are you talking that way to your doctor?

233
00:17:11,770 --> 00:17:13,871
"Doctor"? Who? Him?

234
00:17:14,940 --> 00:17:17,410
I'm sorry. She's still half-asleep.

235
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,011
It's okay.

236
00:17:19,241 --> 00:17:21,380
She's not very healthy right now.

237
00:17:21,381 --> 00:17:24,149
So that could cause her to become hysterical and rude.

238
00:17:24,150 --> 00:17:25,679
What? "Rude"?

239
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,991
Let me check your condition.

240
00:17:28,991 --> 00:17:31,060
Hey, wait. Wait.

241
00:17:31,461 --> 00:17:32,660
Everything seems fine.

242
00:17:33,631 --> 00:17:35,390
Oh, gosh. Wait a minute.

243
00:17:36,491 --> 00:17:37,501
And that's fine too.

244
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:40,231
Goodness, thank you, sir.

245
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,769
Aunt, am I the only one who finds this weird? Really?

246
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:43,770
Am I being strange right now?

247
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:44,770
Yes, you're acting strange.

248
00:17:45,241 --> 00:17:47,270
We just need to take a few basic tests.

249
00:17:48,770 --> 00:17:49,810
Bye then.

250
00:17:52,981 --> 00:17:54,111
Unbelievable.

251
00:17:55,581 --> 00:17:56,810
What's with you?

252
00:17:58,320 --> 00:17:59,420
But he...

253
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,161
You again?

254
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:08,730
Stop chatting and sit.

255
00:18:08,731 --> 00:18:12,060
I can't believe this. Why do you keep following me around?

256
00:18:14,401 --> 00:18:17,300
- Hey. - Stay still. Don't move.

257
00:18:19,901 --> 00:18:22,309
Do you even know how to work this thing?

258
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:23,471
Stop talking.

259
00:18:28,751 --> 00:18:30,680
Seriously, why are you doing this...

260
00:18:30,681 --> 00:18:31,820
Hold your breath.

261
00:18:35,651 --> 00:18:36,691
Good girl.

262
00:18:52,001 --> 00:18:54,570
How many jobs do you have?

263
00:18:54,711 --> 00:18:56,170
Why are you doing this to me?

264
00:18:56,171 --> 00:18:57,510
I'm here to save your life.

265
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:58,840
What are you talking about?

266
00:19:02,610 --> 00:19:03,651
My gosh.

267
00:19:07,050 --> 00:19:09,050
If you go in there with this, you'll die.

268
00:19:09,391 --> 00:19:11,119
Do you know how expensive it is to fix this thing?

269
00:19:11,120 --> 00:19:12,261
I saved your life.

