00:36:05,165 --> 00:36:07,234
I might do something that I would regret.

544
00:36:13,364 --> 00:36:14,475
Ms. Na.

545
00:36:16,504 --> 00:36:17,544
Ms. Na.

546
00:37:19,835 --> 00:37:22,004
Limit your regrets only to me.

547
00:37:22,904 --> 00:37:25,004
Your regrettable action...

548
00:37:25,605 --> 00:37:27,245
could destroy me.

549
00:38:00,075 --> 00:38:01,844
You crazy wench, Na Ji Na!

550
00:38:03,274 --> 00:38:04,884
Gosh. Come on.

551
00:38:07,814 --> 00:38:11,085
- What? My hair? - Yes.

552
00:38:11,725 --> 00:38:14,324
You'll be going through chemo and radiation therapy.

553
00:38:14,325 --> 00:38:15,524
Your hair will fall out quickly.

554
00:38:16,495 --> 00:38:17,825
You've seen it on TV, right?

555
00:38:18,265 --> 00:38:19,693
You might cope better...

556
00:38:19,694 --> 00:38:21,265
if you take care of your hair beforehand.

557
00:38:22,134 --> 00:38:23,564
And that's what I recommend too.

558
00:38:25,227 --> 00:38:27,427
Seeing your hair falling out...

559
00:38:29,057 --> 00:38:30,626
could be harder to watch.

560
00:38:42,177 --> 00:38:46,276
Ever since you were young, you had a nice shaped head.

561
00:38:47,077 --> 00:38:49,116
So whenever I gave you a short haircut,

562
00:38:49,117 --> 00:38:51,347
all the elders in the neighborhood...

563
00:38:51,847 --> 00:38:55,557
would say you look like a cute chestnut...

564
00:38:56,256 --> 00:38:57,856
and give you tons of compliments.

565
00:38:58,557 --> 00:38:59,727
You remember that, right?

566
00:39:00,427 --> 00:39:02,227
Yes, I remember.

567
00:39:02,626 --> 00:39:03,796
Your hair...

568
00:39:06,197 --> 00:39:07,537
will grow.

569
00:39:08,997 --> 00:39:10,267
It'll grow back really fast.

570
00:39:10,767 --> 00:39:12,736
They also sell shampoos that help your hair grow faster.

571
00:39:14,407 --> 00:39:15,435
Right.

572
00:39:15,436 --> 00:39:17,307
Should I also get a haircut?

573
00:39:18,207 --> 00:39:21,177
We can make Sun Kyung shave his head too.

574
00:39:23,977 --> 00:39:26,815
Don't you remember he did that when he went to the army?

575
00:39:26,816 --> 00:39:28,517
He was really ugly.

576
00:39:29,657 --> 00:39:31,227
He looks decent thanks to his hair, so he can't shave his head.

577
00:39:32,086 --> 00:39:36,096
Shaving my head is already enough. Let's not do it to anyone else.

578
00:39:36,097 --> 00:39:37,126
Okay, Auntie?

579
00:39:39,296 --> 00:39:42,267
Gosh, you charming girl. You're such a good girl.

580
00:39:43,396 --> 00:39:47,807
I should go and buy you some hats.

581
00:39:49,207 --> 00:39:50,835
I'll get you pretty ones.

582
00:39:50,836 --> 00:39:53,576
Don't bother. I have a lot of hats.

583
00:39:53,577 --> 00:39:55,246
You even bought me one last time.

584
00:39:55,247 --> 00:39:57,016
Gosh, that's too big.

585
00:39:57,017 --> 00:39:58,716
You have a tiny head.

586
00:39:59,447 --> 00:40:01,157
Let me take a look.

587
00:40:04,660 --> 00:40:05,720
It's about this big.

588
00:40:07,186 --> 00:40:08,396
I'll be right back.

589
00:41:40,816 --> 00:41:42,986
(Absolute rest)

590
00:41:52,997 --> 00:41:55,097
How should I style your hair?

591
00:41:57,097 --> 00:41:59,006
Well...

592
00:42:01,907 --> 00:42:03,307
I want to look like a celebrity.

593
00:42:03,677 --> 00:42:05,246
- Pardon? - Something that celebrities do.

594
00:42:05,247 --> 00:42:09,016
I want a perm that looks really extravagant.

595
00:42:09,017 --> 00:42:10,046
Just like that.

596
00:42:11,316 --> 00:42:12,347
Miss.

597
00:42:13,646 --> 00:42:15,216
That was done with a curling iron.

598
00:42:17,287 --> 00:42:18,356
I want that hairstyle.

599
00:42:22,697 --> 00:42:24,566
There. You're all done.

600
00:42:26,966 --> 00:42:30,497
To be honest, I was a little worried because you came in a patient gown.

601
00:42:31,307 --> 00:42:33,807
We get a few patients from the hospital nearby,

602
00:42:34,137 --> 00:42:35,606
and they come to shave their heads.

603
00:42:38,106 --> 00:42:39,876
This hair looks great on you.

604
00:42:40,677 --> 00:42:43,747
Can we take a photo and upload it on our website?

605
00:42:44,247 --> 00:42:46,287
Your face won't show. It'll just be your hair.

606
00:42:46,747 --> 00:42:48,816
- Just your hair. - Okay.

607
00:42:49,787 --> 00:42:52,026
The curls came out great.

608
00:42:58,066 --> 00:43:00,366
- Are you done? - Wait. Just one more.

609
00:43:00,367 --> 00:43:01,367
I'll take it from here.

610
00:43:03,637 --> 00:43:04,707
It looks so pretty.

611
00:43:05,606 --> 00:43:06,966
You're all done now.

612
00:43:07,807 --> 00:43:08,836
Okay then.

613
00:43:09,836 --> 00:43:11,247
You can shave my head now.

614
00:43:12,707 --> 00:43:13,747
What?

615
00:43:16,447 --> 00:43:18,747
Just shave everything off my head.

616
00:43:21,157 --> 00:43:24,356
I'm sorry. I know you put in a lot of effort to do this for me.

617
00:43:25,287 --> 00:43:27,796
But I wanted to try it one last time.

618
00:43:29,327 --> 00:43:31,566
It won't be your last time. You should come again.

619
00:43:32,296 --> 00:43:33,496
I'll do this for you again.

620
00:43:33,497 --> 00:43:35,236
I'll make sure it comes out even better than today.

621
00:43:36,097 --> 00:43:39,966
Actually, I bet you'll look good with short hair too.

622
00:43:41,407 --> 00:43:43,505
Now that I think of it, it wasn't the hair that came out nice.

623
00:43:43,506 --> 00:43:45,646
You're just pretty to begin with.

624
00:43:48,747 --> 00:43:50,216
Will you be okay?

625
00:43:54,086 --> 00:43:55,086
Yes.

626
00:44:05,966 --> 00:44:07,166
I'll cut it now.

627
00:44:09,896 --> 00:44:10,936
Okay.

628
00:44:13,367 --> 00:44:15,077
- Your nose is bleeding. - My goodness.

629
00:44:15,494 --> 00:44:17,493
- Are you okay? - Oh, yes. I'm sorry.

630
00:44:17,494 --> 00:44:18,633
- Get her a tissue. - I'm fine.

631
00:44:18,634 --> 00:44:20,434
Just a second. Get her a tissue.

632
00:46:01,239 --> 00:46:02,569
Don't cry.

633
00:46:07,279 --> 00:46:08,748
Don't cry.

634
00:46:38,279 --> 00:46:39,478
Don't cry.

635
00:46:41,799 --> 00:46:43,728
Please don't cry.

636
00:47:30,456 --> 00:47:31,695
I'm sorry.

637
00:47:33,765 --> 00:47:35,265
I'm so sorry.

638
00:49:13,195 --> 00:49:14,195
What's going on?

639
00:49:14,836 --> 00:49:16,535
Where am I?

640
00:49:17,296 --> 00:49:18,364
My house.

641
00:49:18,365 --> 00:49:20,365
Why am I in your house?

642
00:49:22,706 --> 00:49:24,435
Was I kidnapped?

643
00:49:24,436 --> 00:49:25,506
Something like that.

644
00:49:26,006 --> 00:49:28,546
Since I dragged you into this dream without your consent.

645
00:49:29,675 --> 00:49:30,746
Dream?

646
00:49:40,226 --> 00:49:41,456
This is a dream?

647
00:49:45,626 --> 00:49:47,365
What... Wow.

648
00:49:48,735 --> 00:49:50,365
It feels so real.

649
00:49:50,936 --> 00:49:51,936
That's right.

650
00:50:00,305 --> 00:50:01,305
What?

651
00:50:12,356 --> 00:50:14,055
(Les Miserables)

652
00:50:18,226 --> 00:50:19,526
You're giving me a headache.

653
00:50:25,865 --> 00:50:27,106
Is this jail?

654
00:50:27,468 --> 00:50:29,338
Did you lock me up?

655
00:50:30,235 --> 00:50:32,405
Is that all you can say to the person who saved your life?

656
00:50:33,192 --> 00:50:34,251
What?

657
00:50:35,246 --> 00:50:36,376
You saved me?

658
00:50:37,316 --> 00:50:38,546
Wasn't that a dream?

659
00:50:38,916 --> 00:50:40,686
No, it wasn't.

660
00:50:42,586 --> 00:50:45,356
Then that dream... No.

661
00:50:45,756 --> 00:50:48,154
That was a dream. It was definitely a dream.

662
00:50:48,155 --> 00:50:50,555
It was a dream. So why...

663
00:50:51,226 --> 00:50:52,265
That dream?

664
00:50:52,526 --> 00:50:56,095
You were crying in my dream earlier.

665
00:50:56,765 --> 00:50:57,836
It was a dream.

666
00:50:58,566 --> 00:51:00,805
I don't eat, sleep, or cry.

667
00:51:01,365 --> 00:51:04,776
I died and you came to my funeral.

668
00:51:05,675 --> 00:51:09,476
You looked at my picture and cried...

669
00:51:23,226 --> 00:51:24,425
I'm not sad.

670
00:51:30,135 --> 00:51:31,765
I'm not sad no matter how much I look at you.

671
00:51:32,735 --> 00:51:35,506
Hey. You startled me.

672
00:51:36,905 --> 00:51:38,875
- Smile. - What?

673
00:51:38,876 --> 00:51:40,505
Smile at me.

674
00:51:40,506 --> 00:51:41,574
Why should I?

675
00:51:41,575 --> 00:51:43,776
I need to know who and what you are.

676
00:51:44,476 --> 00:51:46,186
Will you know if I smile?

677
00:51:56,655 --> 00:51:57,796
Smile again.

678
00:52:09,336 --> 00:52:10,376
I have no idea.

679
00:52:12,675 --> 00:52:14,345
Where are you going?

680
00:52:15,215 --> 00:52:17,275
Where are you going?

681
00:52:17,276 --> 00:52:18,345
Outside.

682
00:52:18,646 --> 00:52:21,086
We need to go somewhere open. It's too dangerous here.

683
00:52:21,756 --> 00:52:24,825
Gosh. Why? Do you think I'll do something to you?

684
00:52:25,885 --> 00:52:29,055
No. I'm afraid I'll do something to you.

685
00:52:30,856 --> 00:52:31,895
Like what?

686
00:52:31,896 --> 00:52:34,996
Who knows? Since I don't know who you are.

687
00:52:35,965 --> 00:52:37,495
Run away if I do.

688
00:52:37,496 --> 00:52:39,006
Run as hard as you can.

689
00:52:40,666 --> 00:52:42,706
Are you sure it's safer outside?

690
00:52:47,445 --> 00:52:48,646
There's nothing dangerous...

691
00:52:50,445 --> 00:52:51,945
since nothing there is alive.

692
00:53:06,365 --> 00:53:09,566
- What is this place? - My subconscious.

693
00:53:10,396 --> 00:53:11,566
Subconscious?

694
00:53:11,965 --> 00:53:13,606
It's like your ocean.

695
00:53:33,985 --> 00:53:36,825
- That was why. - What?

696
00:53:37,095 --> 00:53:39,195
You say this is like my ocean.

697
00:53:40,195 --> 00:53:42,265
So this was how you felt.

698
00:53:42,896 --> 00:53:46,006
That was why you were so prickly.

699
00:53:46,405 --> 00:53:49,035
Don't talk gibberish. Just remember.

700
00:53:49,735 --> 00:53:51,844
Do you really not know me?

701
00:53:51,845 --> 00:53:53,146
No, I don't.

702
00:53:54,175 --> 00:53:55,944
Think before you speak.

703
00:53:55,945 --> 00:53:57,915
Why do I need to think about something like that?

704
00:53:57,916 --> 00:53:59,086
I just know.

705
00:54:04,515 --> 00:54:06,885
I don't need to think to know that you're pretty.

706
00:54:13,066 --> 00:54:14,066
Hey.

707
00:54:15,865 --> 00:54:16,865
Have you been here before?

708
00:54:16,866 --> 00:54:18,336
Obviously, not.

709
00:54:18,365 --> 00:54:20,235
You should think before you talk.

710
00:54:20,706 --> 00:54:23,336
Why? Do you remember seeing me here?

711
00:54:30,715 --> 00:54:32,646
You really must have seen me before.

712
00:54:33,546 --> 00:54:34,586
I have not.

713
00:54:36,086 --> 00:54:37,686
- Then why... - I don't know.

714
00:54:39,055 --> 00:54:42,896
Seriously. You need to learn how to speak again.

715
00:54:45,126 --> 00:54:48,535
You need to make sense. Talk in longer sentences.

716
00:54:48,896 --> 00:54:50,864
What's the use in reading books all the time?

717
00:54:50,865 --> 00:54:53,405
Hey. Be honest with me.

718
00:54:53,566 --> 00:54:56,376
You don't read, do you? You just hold them, don't you?

719
00:54:59,445 --> 00:55:01,106
There's a line that the author wrote.

720
00:55:01,876 --> 00:55:03,646
"Dying is nothing."

721
00:55:04,175 --> 00:55:07,246
"What is frightening is not living to the fullest."

722
00:55:08,916 --> 00:55:10,185
Are you saying that to me?

723
00:55:10,186 --> 00:55:12,086
No. To myself.

724
00:55:13,086 --> 00:55:14,526
Because I'm nothing.

725
00:55:15,996 --> 00:55:17,526
Because I'm not alive.

726
00:55:22,166 --> 00:55:25,106
There's another famous quote by that author.

727
00:55:26,305 --> 00:55:29,106
"The reduction of the universe to one person,"

728
00:55:29,376 --> 00:55:31,535
"and the expansion of one person to a deity."

729
00:55:31,876 --> 00:55:33,675
"That is love."

730
00:55:37,945 --> 00:55:40,646
Remember beautiful things from now on.

731
00:55:41,215 --> 00:55:44,385
Then this place may become...

732
00:55:44,916 --> 00:55:46,555
a little nicer.

733
00:56:33,135 --> 00:56:34,235
Why...

734
00:56:36,606 --> 00:56:38,135
What is this...

735
00:56:46,445 --> 00:56:47,615
Will you choose to do that?

736
00:56:51,316 --> 00:56:52,726
There's not much time.

737
00:56:53,756 --> 00:56:55,226
You need to make a choice.

738
00:57:21,746 --> 00:57:22,916
I'll do it.

739
00:57:28,155 --> 00:57:29,296
I'll do it.

740
00:57:53,546 --> 00:57:55,416
(Ask the world to end before dying.)

741
00:57:56,456 --> 00:57:58,856
(Doom, person I love the most)

742
00:58:03,026 --> 00:58:05,526
(Doom, person I love the most)

743
00:59:41,586 --> 00:59:43,226
Oh, no.

744
01:00:46,856 --> 01:00:49,195
I must be going crazy.

745
01:00:50,695 --> 01:00:52,066
I must be really sick.

746
01:01:08,606 --> 01:01:10,575
(Ms. Soo Ja)

747
01:01:13,015 --> 01:01:15,455
- Auntie. - Where are you?

748
01:01:15,456 --> 01:01:17,385
I left something at my house.

749
01:01:17,856 --> 01:01:18,925
I'll be there soon.

750
01:01:19,626 --> 01:01:20,655
Okay.

751
01:01:33,805 --> 01:01:36,035
(Human)

752
01:01:51,916 --> 01:01:52,956
Hello?

753
01:02:31,856 --> 01:02:32,865
You...

754
01:02:34,865 --> 01:02:36,095
How could you...

755
01:02:39,106 --> 01:02:42,206
How could you forget about me?

756
01:02:42,706 --> 01:02:43,905
Right back at you.

757
01:02:44,476 --> 01:02:46,746
Even if I made that decision,

758
01:02:46,945 --> 01:02:48,845
you should have recognized me right away.

759
01:02:49,146 --> 01:02:51,675
You should have remembered me.

760
01:02:52,546 --> 01:02:53,646
That's my fault?

761
01:02:54,345 --> 01:02:55,956
Who told you to make that decision?

762
01:02:57,385 --> 01:03:00,554
You did whatever you wanted without talking to me.

763
01:03:00,555 --> 01:03:02,995
You know what? Even when you lost your memory,

764
01:03:02,996 --> 01:03:04,856
your nasty temper didn't go away.

765
01:03:05,296 --> 01:03:07,496
Did you find me handsome even when you lost your memory?

766
01:04:23,276 --> 01:04:27,175
(Doom at Your Service)

767
01:04:27,569 --> 01:04:29,208
We can't escape...

768
01:04:30,688 --> 01:04:32,328
our fate, right?

769
01:04:34,646 --> 01:04:37,115
So we should accept it now.

770
01:04:37,856 --> 01:04:39,756
Will it hurt a lot when I die?

771
01:04:40,285 --> 01:04:44,226
You knew that I would be making this decision, right?

772
01:04:45,095 --> 01:04:48,695
I don't know what I will decide.

773
01:04:50,095 --> 01:04:51,265
We should go.

774
01:04:51,996 --> 01:04:53,035
Bye.

775
01:04:54,135 --> 01:04:55,805
I didn't give up yet.

776
01:04:56,376 --> 01:04:58,675
- Help us. - Accept it.

777
01:04:59,898 --> 01:05:00,998
I love you.

778
01:05:01,376 --> 01:05:03,615
Thank you for loving me.
